<i> I'll be able to get</i>
<i> my width of the blade</i>

05:24.325 --> 05:26.283
<i> and the length of the blade</i>
<i> as quickly as possible.</i>

05:26.327 --> 05:29.077
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

05:29.121 --> 05:30.370
Watch out.

05:30.414 --> 05:31.788
- I'm ready to battle.

05:31.832 --> 05:33.206
- Now, is it possible to forge

05:33.250 --> 05:35.542
an entire blade out of one
of those hammerheads?

05:35.586 --> 05:37.085
Is that--
- Yes, shouldn't be a problem.

05:37.129 --> 05:40.464
Now, what is the steel?
What is that hammer made out of?

05:40.507 --> 05:42.632
- Right.
- I chose the hammer steel

05:42.676 --> 05:44.301
because it could take a beating.

05:44.345 --> 05:46.636
It's a little bit harder
metal; I know it will get hard.

05:46.680 --> 05:50.349
I am ADD, so I'm
switching back from the press

05:50.392 --> 05:52.100
<i> to the hammer</i>
<i> to the press to the hammer.</i>

05:52.144 --> 05:54.478
<i> I can't make up my mind</i>
<i> what I want to use.</i>

05:54.521 --> 05:56.396
- Eric moving very quickly.

05:56.440 --> 05:58.815
This is a three-hour
competition,

05:58.859 --> 06:00.734
and I hope that he's
pacing himself.

06:00.778 --> 06:03.695
- It only gets hotter
as we progress.

06:03.739 --> 06:05.238
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

06:05.282 --> 06:07.491
- Always waiting for
the steel to heat up.

06:07.534 --> 06:08.867
I chose a file.

06:08.911 --> 06:10.118
I know that the file
will harden.

06:10.162 --> 06:11.745
<i> Once you get it in the forge,</i>

06:11.789 --> 06:13.455
<i> everything's starting</i>
<i> to heat up.</i>

06:13.499 --> 06:15.457
<i> I just start crushing metal,</i>
<i> putting it in the press,</i>

06:15.501 --> 06:18.043
<i> and seeing if your welds</i>
<i> are gonna take or not.</i>

06:18.087 --> 06:20.045
<i> - I'm going with a hammer.</i>

06:20.089 --> 06:22.172
<i> I feel there's enough material</i>
<i> in the hammerhead</i>

06:22.216 --> 06:24.174
that I can pull the blade
out long enough.

06:24.218 --> 06:26.051
Let's do a handle.

06:26.095 --> 06:27.844
<i> Gonna try to horseshoe</i>
<i> the tang.</i>

06:27.888 --> 06:29.763
So I'm gonna try to wrap
that around the wood,

06:29.807 --> 06:31.348
so I'll have, like,
this exposed tang

06:31.392 --> 06:35.477
on either side with
the wood core in the middle.

06:35.521 --> 06:37.187
- I like it.
It's bold.

06:37.231 --> 06:39.022
He's taking a chance.
- It's so outside the box.

06:39.066 --> 06:40.774
<i> - I got plan B if I need to.</i>

06:40.818 --> 06:42.275
<i> I'm really hoping</i>
<i> this works out.</i>

06:42.319 --> 06:44.778
We'll see.

06:44.822 --> 06:47.322
- One hour has already elapsed.

06:47.366 --> 06:50.575
You have just two hours
remaining to finish your work.

06:50.619 --> 06:53.036
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

06:53.080 --> 06:55.122
- So I've got my files stacked
in this thing

06:55.165 --> 06:58.333
and welded together this way,
and I'm forging the tip.

06:58.377 --> 07:01.837
<i> So as I was forging the tip</i>
<i> out, I noticed my weld</i>

07:01.880 --> 07:04.631
at the very tip not
lined up correctly.

07:04.675 --> 07:06.883
It starts opening up.

07:06.927 --> 07:08.510
<i> So I'm taking it over</i>
<i> to the chop saw.</i>

07:08.554 --> 07:09.803
Cuttin'.

07:09.847 --> 07:11.888
<i> I hope I have enough material.</i>

07:11.932 --> 07:14.015
<i> Cutting that last little</i>
<i> 1/2-inch piece off,</i>

07:14.059 --> 07:15.225
<i> go back over,</i>

07:15.269 --> 07:16.726
<i> start forging the tip again.</i>

07:16.770 --> 07:19.187
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

07:19.231 --> 07:21.064
<i> - I'm at the grinder.</i>
<i> I need to make sure</i>

07:21.108 --> 07:22.732
<i> that I have enough</i>
<i> cutting edge,</i>

07:22.776 --> 07:25.694
