25:39.747 --> 25:42.915
So I think now
it's time for me to go home

25:42.959 --> 25:45.167
and start fighting fires again.

25:45.211 --> 25:47.753
<i> [dramatic music]</i>

25:47.797 --> 25:49.505
- Eric, Jared, congratulations.

25:49.549 --> 25:51.507
Your weapons were strong
enough to propel you

25:51.551 --> 25:53.551
into this final round
of competition,

25:53.594 --> 25:55.594
which means you're both one step
closer to the title

25:55.638 --> 25:59.515
of "Forged in Fire" champion
and that check for $10,000.

25:59.559 --> 26:01.392
Now we're sending you back
to your home forges

26:01.435 --> 26:03.811
to create an iconic blade
from history...

26:03.854 --> 26:06.188
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

26:06.232 --> 26:08.440
The hunga munga.

26:08.484 --> 26:10.943
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

26:10.987 --> 26:12.695
<i> The term hunga munga refers</i>

26:12.738 --> 26:15.155
<i>to a variety of central African</i>
<i> throwing knives,</i>

26:15.199 --> 26:17.324
<i> all of which feature</i>
<i> a series of double-edged</i>

26:17.368 --> 26:19.493
<i> iron blades attached</i>
<i> to a rawhide handle.</i>

26:19.537 --> 26:21.120
<i> The hunga munga was</i>
<i> not only formidable</i>

26:21.163 --> 26:22.538
<i> in hand-to-hand combat,</i>

26:22.582 --> 26:24.248
<i> but could be thrown</i>
<i> from a distance,</i>

26:24.292 --> 26:25.708
<i> with some reports</i>
<i> claiming it had</i>

26:25.751 --> 26:28.502
<i> a throwing range</i>
<i> of up to 250 feet.</i>

26:28.546 --> 26:31.005
<i> As armor was not used often</i>
<i> in central Africa,</i>

26:31.048 --> 26:34.008
<i> this type of throwing iron</i>
<i> was particularly devastating.</i>

26:34.051 --> 26:36.343
<i> Hunga munga was</i>
<i> often very valuable</i>

26:36.387 --> 26:38.095
<i> and could be traded for goods.</i>

26:38.139 --> 26:39.555
<i> The hunga munga was</i>
<i> also wielded</i>

26:39.599 --> 26:41.890
<i> by Buffy Summers</i>
<i> in the cult series</i>

26:41.934 --> 26:44.184
"Buffy the Vampire Slayer."

26:44.228 --> 26:46.270
- First thing
I thought was, "[bleep]."

26:46.314 --> 26:48.272
[laughing]

26:48.316 --> 26:50.733
<i> I was not expecting that.</i>

26:50.776 --> 26:53.902
- Your weapon must fall within
the following parameters:

26:53.946 --> 26:55.738
it must have a sharpened head,

26:55.781 --> 26:58.490
crescent blade,
a spear, and a spike.

26:58.534 --> 27:00.367
You must also include
a handle arm

27:00.411 --> 27:03.704
with a sharpened spike
above the handle.

27:03.748 --> 27:06.915
It must be an effective, working
version of that deadly weapon.

27:06.959 --> 27:09.627
However, we want you to make
something that's unique,

27:09.670 --> 27:12.421
that could only come
from your forge.

27:12.465 --> 27:15.132
- I'm looking forward to decking
this hunga munga out

27:15.176 --> 27:16.800
and putting my own
signature style

27:16.844 --> 27:18.969
in the details
and decorative work.

27:19.013 --> 27:21.055
<i> - I'm trying to think of how</i>
<i> complicated this thing</i>

27:21.098 --> 27:22.306
will be to build.

27:22.350 --> 27:24.475
It's complicated forging.

27:24.518 --> 27:26.185
- You will have five days
at your home forge

27:26.228 --> 27:27.519
to complete this challenge.

27:27.563 --> 27:29.313
At the end of those five days,

27:29.357 --> 27:31.273
you will return and present
your finished weapons

27:31.317 --> 27:33.442
to our panel of expert judges.

27:33.486 --> 27:35.235
Only after they've
subjected your weapons

27:35.279 --> 27:37.655
to a series of brutal tests

27:37.698 --> 27:40.949
will they declare one of you
the "Forged in Fire" champion

27:40.993 --> 27:43.494
who walks away with that check
for 10 grand.

27:43.537 --> 27:46.121
Good luck, bladesmiths.
We'll see you in five days.

27:46.165 --> 27:48.290
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

27:48.334 --> 27:51.210
<i> [driving rock music]</i>

27:51.253 --> 27:53.962
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

27:54.006 --> 27:56.965
<i> - First day. Really happy</i>
<i> to be back in my shop.</i>

27:57.009 --> 28:00.928
I have never made anything
even remotely like this before.

28:00.971 --> 28:04.139
<i> This is, like,</i>
<i> a cross between a sword,</i>

28:04.183 --> 28:07.810
boomerang, chakram...

28:07.853 --> 28:10.479
battle axe.

28:10.523 --> 28:11.689
I got to plan this out.

28:11.732 --> 28:13.148
I'm gonna start with this blade,

28:13.192 --> 28:14.608
then pull this off
from the side,

28:14.652 --> 28:16.318
and then start working
the spike in.

28:16.362 --> 28:18.278
This is a wild build.

28:18.322 --> 28:19.947
[pounding]

28:19.990 --> 28:22.825
<i> [percussive music]</i>

28:22.868 --> 28:24.910
So I'm gonna have to heat
this all up.

28:24.954 --> 28:27.454
I'm gonna have
to drive this down.

28:27.498 --> 28:29.081
<i> It's almost a chess game.</i>

28:29.125 --> 28:31.166
I've got to think, like,
five moves ahead on this thing,

28:31.210 --> 28:32.835
<i> 'cause if I screw up once,</i>

28:32.878 --> 28:34.336
<i> it could completely ruin</i>
<i> the piece of steel I got,</i>

28:34.380 --> 28:35.421
<i> and I got to start over.</i>

28:35.464 --> 28:37.256
[pounding]

28:37.299 --> 28:41.427
This chunk here, hopefully
turn into my sickle blade here.

28:41.470 --> 28:44.179
[whirring]

28:44.223 --> 28:45.681
Maybe if I heat this area here,

28:45.725 --> 28:48.100
swing this out of the way
here...

28:48.144 --> 28:50.769
[grinding and hammering]

28:50.813 --> 28:53.063
I'm gonna push that
up into there.

28:53.107 --> 28:54.857
Then I can push this around.

28:54.900 --> 29:01.864
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

29:01.907 --> 29:06.368
That spear point's
