29:06.412 --> 29:09.371
<i> [energetic music]</i>

29:09.415 --> 29:12.875
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

29:12.918 --> 29:15.169
<i> - It's day one.</i>
<i> I got a sheet of metal,</i>

29:15.212 --> 29:18.422
<i> and I'm gonna be slicing</i>
<i> the shape out of it</i>

29:18.466 --> 29:19.882
<i> and forge out the blade</i>

29:19.925 --> 29:22.926
<i> from a general shape</i>
<i> that I cut out.</i>

29:22.970 --> 29:25.929
So what's left to do now,
put it in the forge,

29:25.973 --> 29:28.182
and get it heated up
and drawn out.

29:28.225 --> 29:29.808
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

29:29.852 --> 29:31.685
<i> Making this hunga munga's</i>
<i> a lot different</i>

29:31.729 --> 29:33.604
<i> than making a movie prop.</i>

29:33.647 --> 29:36.565
<i> A prop doesn't really need</i>
<i> to do the task.</i>

29:36.609 --> 29:38.901
For instance,
cutting or slicing or killing.

29:38.944 --> 29:42.863
This actually does have
to perform a specific task.

29:42.907 --> 29:45.491
<i> So this is definitely</i>
<i> a lot more challenging.</i>

29:45.534 --> 29:49.912
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

29:49.955 --> 29:51.747
<i> This is the hardest part.</i>

29:51.791 --> 29:54.917
<i> I mean, moving metal,</i>
<i> working with the heat--</i>

29:54.960 --> 29:58.086
<i> this is a heavy,</i>
<i> heavy, big blade.</i>

29:58.130 --> 29:59.087
[grunts]

29:59.131 --> 30:00.589
<i> I'm very tired,</i>

30:00.633 --> 30:01.882
<i> and I just don't have</i>
<i> the strength</i>

30:01.926 --> 30:03.383
<i> to really move</i>
<i> the metal quickly.</i>

30:03.427 --> 30:05.052
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

30:05.095 --> 30:07.930
Whoa!
[laughs]

30:07.973 --> 30:10.474
I feel like I am going
to fall over.

30:10.518 --> 30:14.895
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

30:14.939 --> 30:17.022
<i> - Day three.</i>
<i> I'm feeling pretty good.</i>

30:17.066 --> 30:19.358
<i> Got done with the forging,</i>
<i> did normalizing,</i>

30:19.401 --> 30:22.110
<i> and now I'm getting everything</i>
<i> prepped and ready for quench.</i>

30:22.154 --> 30:23.403
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

30:23.447 --> 30:25.697
That looks badass.

30:25.741 --> 30:27.491
So you know, right now,

30:27.535 --> 30:29.576
I'm just kind of getting a feel
